## 5. ParseStats — Always Report Data Quality

Every `ParseResult` MUST include a fully populated `ParseStats` object:

```ts
interface ParseStats {
  totalRows: number;
  parsedCount: number;
  skippedCount: number;
  duplicateCount: number;
  currencyDetected: string | undefined;
  hasProductCodes: boolean;   // ← critical: gates image enrichment UX
  hasDiscounts: boolean;      // ← informs layout selection UI
  warnings: RowWarning[];
}
```

**UI rules (ProductDataInput):**
- If `isMobilelandImageEnabled() && !stats.hasProductCodes` → show amber warning:
  _"No product codes found — add a Šifra/Code column to enable image auto-fetch"_
- If `!isMobilelandImageEnabled() && stats.hasProductCodes` → show blue info:
  _"Product codes detected but online enrichment is disabled — configure PUBLIC_MOBILELAND_IMAGE_BASE"_
- If `stats.hasDiscounts` → suggest "Sale Discount" layout in the layout picker

